Adjust rack to top position, then preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry
all produce. Halve, deseed, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1}. Halve, peel,
and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2},
separating whites from greens. Zest 1 tsp zest from @lime{1}; halve lime. Thinly
slice @jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat.

Melt @butter{2%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add
@tomato paste{3%tablespoon} and half the @southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}.
Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Stir in ¼ cup water. Simmer until slightly
thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat;
transfer to a #small bowl{}. In a separate small bowl, combine jalapeño, juice
from lime, @sugar{½%teaspoon}, and salt.

Add @black beans{13.4%ounce}(liquid reserved) and their liquid,
@chipotle powder{¼%teaspoon}, remaining Southwest Spice Blend, and a pinch of
salt to same #pot{}. Cook on high, stirring occasionally, until thickened,
~{8-10%minutes}. Remove from heat. Mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until
mostly smooth. Season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{}
over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and onion. Cook, stirring, until
browned and softened, ~{10-12%minutes}. (TIP: If veggies brown too quickly, stir
in a splash of water.) Add scallion whites and @cumin{1%teaspoon}. Cook until
fragrant, about ~{1%minute}. Remove from heat. Season with salt and pepper.

Place @flour tortillas{2} on a work surface. Divide beans and veggies among the
center of tortillas. Tightly roll tortillas around filling, then place seam
sides down in a #baking dish{}. Top with sauce and @pepper jack cheese{½%cup}.
Bake on top rack of oven until cheese has melted, about ~{2%minutes}.

In another small bowl, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, lime zest, and 1 TBSP
water. Season with salt and pepper. Top baked enchiladas with lime crema,
scallion greens, and as much pickled jalapeño (draining before adding) as you
like.